The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their application in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer science (cs). The paper specifically focuses on training CNNs on multi-megapixel images, which requires a novel approach due to memory constraints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also proposes a new method for training CNNs, which involves exploiting the locality of operations in modern CNNs. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper deals with memory constraints and optimization, which may make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
